      "name": "Controlled-experiment validation of hemolysis index predictions",
      "description": "For MRL 5 Class III VAD devices, absolute hemolysis index predictions shall be validated by means of a controlled experiment in which operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, inlet hematocrit, fluid temperature) are independently set and measured under laboratory conditions with calibrated instrumentation traceable to national standards. Observational or registry-based evidence alone does not satisfy this requirement because confounding variables in clinical use cannot be adequately controlled to isolate model prediction error from patient-specific variability.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
    }
