    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors and the supporting validation evidence. The observational study comparing CFD hemolysis predictions against the 312-patient clinical registry was judged to provide sufficiently broad operating-condition coverage to support the hemolysis credibility claim. The team noted that the registry dataset spans real-world patient variability exceeding any single bench experiment and concluded that the validation evidence, taken together with the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, is adequate to accept the model for the stated COU. Gaps in numerical solver error, use error, test samples, and equivalency of input parameters were acknowledged but deemed acceptable given the breadth of clinical observational data. Decision: Accepted.",
